<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="_editing_the_ceres_homepage_with_the_shopbuilder">3.5.3. Editing the Ceres homepage with the ShopBuilder</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the preview area, you can edit elements to adjust the page to your individual needs.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing elements in the preview area:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The ShopBuilder is opened.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Move the cursor over the element you want to edit.<br>
→ The context menu is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click <strong>Edit</strong> in the upper right corner.
→ The <strong>Settings</strong> bar is displayed.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-elements-shop-builder">Table 11</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The homepage of your online store is modified according to the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can also remove elements.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Removing elements from the preview area:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » ShopBuilder</strong>.<br>
→ The ShopBuilder is opened.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>homepage</strong>.<br>
→ The preview area of the homepage is opened.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the preview area, move the cursor over the element you want to remove.<br>
→ The context menu is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click <strong>Delete</strong> in the upper right corner to remove the element.<br>
→ The element is removed and the surrounding elements are regrouped.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The homepage of your online store is modified according to the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
